## The Week at a Glance

- 🔴 **Active credential-theft campaign targeting your workforce:** The ACR Stealer campaign is actively stealing browser credentials and authentication tokens from enterprise environments using convincing on-screen prompts; your employees do not need to click an attachment for this to succeed.
- 🔴 **Exchange Server 2016/2019 support ends October 2026, no exceptions:** Microsoft has confirmed no further extensions; organizations still running these servers face an unpatched email infrastructure within 100 days, a direct compliance and cyber insurance risk.
- 🟡 **Post-quantum encryption is now shipping in Windows:** Microsoft has begun delivering quantum-safe encryption in Windows 11 and Server 2025 updates; organizations in regulated industries should begin planning adoption timelines now.
- 🟢 **New Zero Trust controls for AI, web, and private app traffic in preview:** Microsoft Entra is extending identity-based access verification to AI agents and all network traffic; no action required yet, but relevant for Zero Trust roadmap planning.

*Sources: [Microsoft Security Blog - ACR Stealer](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/16/acr-stealer-two-observed-intrusion-chains-amid-increased-threat-activity/) · [Exchange Team Blog - ESU End Date](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/reminder-exchange-2016-and-2019-esu-program-ends-in-october-2026/ba-p/4539033) · [Microsoft Security Community - Post-Quantum Windows](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-security-community/new-windows-features-to-secure-today-s-data-in-a-post-quantum/ba-p/4523370)*

---

## Why This Week Matters

Two distinct threat vectors are demanding leadership attention simultaneously: an active, spreading credential-theft campaign that bypasses traditional email-attachment defenses, and a firm deadline that will leave on-premises Exchange servers permanently unpatched in less than 100 days. The one thing leadership must understand is that both risks have a fixed clock: the ACR Stealer campaign is live right now, and October 2026 will not move. Decisions delayed past this briefing cycle will narrow options and increase remediation cost significantly.

*Sources: [Microsoft Security Blog - ACR Stealer](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/16/acr-stealer-two-observed-intrusion-chains-amid-increased-threat-activity/) · [Exchange Team Blog - ESU End Date](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/reminder-exchange-2016-and-2019-esu-program-ends-in-october-2026/ba-p/4539033)*

---

## Risk & Compliance

- 🔴 **[ACR Stealer credential-theft campaign](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/16/acr-stealer-two-observed-intrusion-chains-amid-increased-threat-activity/):** Active attacks are stealing browser credentials, session tokens, and sensitive documents from enterprise environments using ClickFix lures that appear as on-screen instructions; stolen tokens can bypass multi-factor authentication, creating direct exposure under SOC 2, HIPAA, and cyber insurance requirements. Act immediately: engage your security team or managed security provider to validate detection coverage this week.

- 🔴 **[Exchange Server 2016/2019 ESU program ends October 2026](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/reminder-exchange-2016-and-2019-esu-program-ends-in-october-2026/ba-p/4539033):** Microsoft has confirmed no further extensions; after October, any vulnerabilities discovered in these email servers will go unpatched permanently, creating a regulatory compliance gap under HIPAA, CMMC, and most cyber insurance policies. Organizations without a migration plan approved and funded today are running out of runway.

- 🔴 **[July 2026 Exchange Server Security Updates](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/released-july-2026-exchange-server-security-updates/ba-p/4534146):** Microsoft has released July security patches for Exchange SE, 2019, and 2016; organizations enrolled in the Period 2 ESU program must apply these now, as unpatched on-premises email servers are among the most targeted assets in enterprise environments.

- 🟡 **[Post-quantum encryption now available in Windows 11 and Server 2025](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-security-community/new-windows-features-to-secure-today-s-data-in-a-post-quantum/ba-p/4523370):** ML-KEM hybrid key exchange and composite algorithms are now shipping in July Windows updates; organizations subject to NIST CSF, FedRAMP, or CMMC should begin planning adoption timelines, as regulators are increasingly treating quantum-safe cryptography as a forward compliance requirement.

- 🟡 **[Purview DLP for Copilot: external email restriction in preview](https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-365/roadmap?id=561552):** A new control to prevent Microsoft 365 Copilot and Copilot Chat from processing emails sent by external parties is now in preview, with general availability targeted for January 2027; organizations in regulated industries should evaluate this control as part of their AI governance and data-protection posture ahead of GA.

- 🟡 **[Purview DLP alert data now enriched in Defender Graph API](https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-365/roadmap?id=558681):** DLP event details are being added to the Microsoft Graph API, making it easier to feed compliance signals into SIEM tools and automated workflows; relevant to SOC 2 and HIPAA audit requirements, and worth planning integration work within the next 30 days.

- 🟢 **[Zero Trust extended to AI agents and all traffic via Entra Internet/Private Access](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-entra-blog/secure-ai-web-and-private-apps-with-zero-trust/ba-p/4516387):** Microsoft Entra now extends Zero Trust verification to AI agent traffic and all internet and private app access, closing an implicit-trust gap where non-human workloads and network traffic previously operated outside identity-based controls; currently in preview, no immediate action required.

- 🟢 **[Purview retention-based file archiving for OneDrive and SharePoint](https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-365/roadmap?id=561208):** Inactive files under retention can soon be moved to lower-cost storage automatically without breaking compliance or Copilot discoverability; preview expected August 2026, GA in September.

*Sources: [Microsoft Security Blog - ACR Stealer](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/16/acr-stealer-two-observed-intrusion-chains-amid-increased-threat-activity/) · [Exchange Team Blog - July Security Updates](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/released-july-2026-exchange-server-security-updates/ba-p/4534146) · [Microsoft 365 Roadmap](https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-365/roadmap?id=561552)*

