## Cost & Licensing

- **Exchange migration carries licensing implications.** Moving from Exchange 2016/2019 to Exchange Online requires Microsoft 365 licenses that may not be in the current budget. Organizations with a large on-premises footprint should initiate a licensing cost analysis now to avoid a rushed procurement in September or October.
- **Purview retention-based archiving** (coming in September 2026) may reduce SharePoint and OneDrive storage costs by automatically tiering inactive content. Organizations paying overage storage fees should flag this for a cost-benefit review before GA.
- **Defender Experts managed service** is highlighted this week as a way to convert raw threat intelligence into decisions; organizations without a dedicated SOC should evaluate whether a managed detection service is more cost-effective than expanding internal headcount to address the current threat environment.

*Sources: [Exchange Team Blog - ESU End Date](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/reminder-exchange-2016-and-2019-esu-program-ends-in-october-2026/ba-p/4539033) · [Microsoft 365 Roadmap - Retention Archiving](https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-365/roadmap?id=561208) · [Microsoft Security Blog - Defender Experts](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/15/turning-threat-intelligence-into-decisive-action-with-defender-experts/)*

