## Planning Horizon

- **Immediately - [ACR Stealer credential-theft campaign](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/16/acr-stealer-two-observed-intrusion-chains-amid-increased-threat-activity/):** Direct your security team or managed security provider to confirm detection and response coverage for ClickFix-style credential theft this week, and authorize a targeted employee awareness communication.

- **Immediately - [July 2026 Exchange Server Security Updates](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/released-july-2026-exchange-server-security-updates/ba-p/4534146):** Confirm with your IT team that July patches have been applied to all on-premises Exchange servers; this is a prerequisite for ESU program access and cannot be deferred.

- **Within 30 days - [Exchange 2016/2019 ESU end date - October 2026](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/reminder-exchange-2016-and-2019-esu-program-ends-in-october-2026/ba-p/4539033):** Approve a migration plan and budget for any remaining on-premises Exchange infrastructure; vendor and IT coordination must begin now to complete migration before the hard October deadline.

- **Within 30 days - [Purview DLP enrichment in Defender Graph API](https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-365/roadmap?id=558681):** Assign your compliance and security operations teams to evaluate integration of DLP event data into existing SIEM or audit workflows before this capability reaches general availability.

- **Within 60 days - [Post-quantum encryption in Windows 11 and Server 2025](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-security-community/new-windows-features-to-secure-today-s-data-in-a-post-quantum/ba-p/4523370):** Ask your CISO or security architect to assess which data classifications and regulated workloads should be prioritized for quantum-safe cryptography adoption, particularly for FedRAMP, CMMC, or NIST CSF-aligned environments.

- **Within 60 days - [Entra Internet Access and Private Access Zero Trust preview](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-entra-blog/secure-ai-web-and-private-apps-with-zero-trust/ba-p/4516387):** Evaluate whether a pilot of these controls fits the organization's Zero Trust roadmap; extending identity-based verification to all traffic, including AI agents, closes a significant implicit-trust gap before these patterns become standard attacker targets.

- **Before August 2026 - [Purview retention-based file archiving preview](https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-365/roadmap?id=561208):** Identify stakeholders in legal, compliance, and IT to participate in the preview and validate that archiving policies align with retention schedules and e-discovery requirements before September GA.

- **Before January 2027 - [Purview DLP restriction on external email processing by Copilot](https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-365/roadmap?id=561552):** Begin a policy review now so that DLP configurations are ready to enforce external-email restrictions in Copilot when the control reaches general availability, particularly for organizations in healthcare, finance, or legal sectors.

*Sources: [Microsoft Security Blog - ACR Stealer](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/16/acr-stealer-two-observed-intrusion-chains-amid-increased-threat-activity/) · [Exchange Team Blog - ESU End Date](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/reminder-exchange-2016-and-2019-esu-program-ends-in-october-2026/ba-p/4539033) · [Microsoft 365 Roadmap](https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-365/roadmap?id=561552)*

